{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AH6EDEMgnmngvoM9HawGbi","type":"tool_result","content":"  3430→4. **Stale state persistence is architectural.** Ralph's memory model (load once, write repeatedly) is fundamentally incompatible with external state modifications. The fix requires either: (a) re-reading state from disk on each iteration, or (b) treating `done` as an irreversible terminal state.\n  3431→5. **Cost controls are absent.** There is no budget limit, no session cap, no idle detection. Ralph will spend indefinitely.\n  3432→6. **The retro/issues log itself is part of the waste.** Each session appends ~20 lines to `.session-issues.md` (now 454 lines) and occasionally generates a retro (this file is now 3,400+ lines). The documentation of the problem now costs more than the problem itself would cost to fix.\n  3433→\n  3434→### 5. Action Items\n  3435→\n  3436→| Priority | Action | Owner | Status |\n  3437→|----------|--------|-------|--------|\n  3438→| **P0** | **STOP RALPH IMMEDIATELY.** Kill the process. There is zero work remaining. 82 no-op sessions have wasted ~$325. Every additional session wastes another ~$2. | Human operator | **OVERDUE — first requested session 17, now session 103** |\n  3439→| **P0** | **Fix state reversion bug.** Make `done` an irreversible terminal status in Ralph's state machine. If disk says `done`, Ralph must not overwrite with any earlier status. | Developer | Not started |\n  3440→| **P1** | **Add sprint-complete exit.** On session start: if all stories are `done`, log \"sprint complete\" and `process.exit(0)`. | Developer | Not started |\n  3441→| **P1** | **Add idle session circuit breaker.** If 3+ consecutive sessions produce zero state transitions, halt and send alert (not just log). | Developer | Not started |\n  3442→| **P1** | **Add cost ceiling.** Configure a maximum API spend. When reached, halt. | Developer | Not started |\n  3443→| **P2** | **Tag no-op sessions in cost tracking.** The \"unknown\" bucket ($213.67, 26%) should be attributed to no-op overhead. | Developer | Not started |\n  3444→| **P2** | **Write post-mortem.** Formal document on the 82-session state corruption loop for future architectural reference. | PM | Not started |\n  3445→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JQsBcDxpsLYNtpYBocjjXC","session_id":"4fd76e9c-9404-4401-aba8-f35f9a3f2caa","uuid":"a4abf553-1fce-4bab-a357-d937ea90a670","timestamp":"2026-03-28T07:54:49.963Z"}
